Package: TSQCA
Type: Package
Title: Threshold Sweep Extensions for Qualitative Comparative Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Yuki", "Toyoda", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "yuki.toyoda.ds@hosei.ac.jp")
Description: 
    Provides threshold sweep methods for Qualitative Comparative Analysis (QCA). 
    Implements Condition Threshold Sweep-Single (CTS-S), Condition Threshold 
    Sweep-Multiple (CTS-M), Outcome Threshold Sweep (OTS), and Dual Threshold 
    Sweep (DTS) for systematic exploration of threshold calibration effects on 
    crisp-set QCA results. These methods extend traditional robustness approaches 
    by treating threshold variation as an exploratory tool for discovering causal 
    structures. Based on Ragin (2008) <doi:10.7208/chicago/9780226702797.001.0001>, 
    Du≈üa (2019) <doi:10.1007/978-3-319-75668-4>, and robustness protocols by 
    Oana and Schneider (2024) <doi:10.1177/00491241211036158>.
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.0)
